      "detailed_descriptions": {
        "INC-Baroda_House_MX-204-cfabf4bc_1771263950.9": "A ospfNbrStateChange trap signifies that ifies   that   there  has been a change in the state of a non-   virtual OSPF neighbor.   This  trap  should  be   generated  when  the  neighbor  state regresses   (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full  to  1-Way  or   Down)  or progresses to a terminal state (e.g.,   2-Way or Full).  When an  neighbor  transitions   from  or  to Full on non-broadcast multi-access   and broadcast networks, the trap should be gen-   erated  by the designated router.  A designated   router transitioning to Down will be  noted  by   ospfIfStateChange.",
        "INC-Baroda_House_MX-204-cfabf4bc_1771263951.888": "A ospfNbrStateChange trap signifies that ifies   that   there  has been a change in the state of a non-   virtual OSPF neighbor.   This  trap  should  be   generated  when  the  neighbor  state regresses   (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full  to  1-Way  or   Down)  or progresses to a terminal state (e.g.,   2-Way or Full).  When an  neighbor  transitions   from  or  to Full on non-broadcast multi-access   and broadcast networks, the trap should be gen-   erated  by the designated router.  A designated   router transitioning to Down will be  noted  by   ospfIfStateChange.",
